85 Benfica Roofing Inc. located in Toronto, Ontario is looking for full-time Roofers with a minimum 3 years experience.

Duties include:

installing, repairing or replacing shingles, shakes and other roofing tiles on sloped roofs of buildings;
installing sheet metal flashings;
installing, repairing or replacing built-up roofing systems using materials such as asphalt saturated felts and hot asphalt and gravel;
applying waterproof coatings to concrete or other masonry surfaces below or above ground level;
installing, repairing or replacing single-ply roofing system using waterproof sheet materials such as modified plastics, elastomeric or other asphaltic compositions.
$26.50 - $28.00 per hour.

Special consideration will be given to the various underrepresented groups.

TO APPLY:
Please send resume to: 85benficaroofing@gmail.com

We are looking for a full-time Truck Driver with a minimum of 2 years experience.

Duties include:

Drive and operate trucks;
Operate and drive straight or articulated trucks to transport heavy construction equipment; load and unload heavy construction equipment from truck;
Drive lighter, special purpose trucks;
Load and unload goods; Tarping and ensuring safety and security of cargo;
Inspect trucks.
AZ license required.

$32-$35 per hour.

Special consideration will be given to the various underrepresented groups.

TO APPLY:
Please send resume to: info@torcanlift.com

We are a reputable and fast-growing wholesaler of Smartphone & Electronics Accessories and Repair Parts in British Columbia, Canada. We are seeking a highly skilled and experienced full-stack web developer to join our team to streamline the online bulk purchasing process and e-commerce platform, as well as create new functions for our website.

 

Education and Experience Required:

Bachelor's degree in Computer Science or related subject is required;
Minimum of 5 years of experience in web development;
Minimum of 1 year of experience working on e-commerce shopping systems;
Familiar work with Linux environment;
Experience with HTML5, CSS, and web-base UI development;
Knowledge of at least one python backend frameworks such as Django or Flask;
Knowledge of at least one of Javascript front-end framework such as Vue and React;
Experience with SQL databases(MySQL, PostgreSQL as plus);
Strong experience using CI/CD automation/build tools and version control tools such as Git;
Strong knowledge of distribute database system such as Redis.
 

Key duties:

In this role, you will be responsible for strategic direction of the function within the relevant part of the business, combined with a solid conceptual and practical grounding in both the function and/or area of expertise, as well as related subject areas. You will be responsible for ensuring that all aspects of development and implementation and meet the highest quality standards, with a focus on creating scalable web services that deliver a consistently excellent experience to our clients.

Develop, write, modify, integrate, and test website-related code and web application interfaces;
Develop and implement procedures for ongoing website revision;
Conduct tests and analyze data to monitor quality, security, user interface experiences, and identify areas for improvement;
Monitor and maintain website functionality;
Participate in website architecture and design in collaboration with designers or clients;
Research and evaluate a variety of interactive media software products;
Integrating and maintaining online sales system, inventory management system, and financial system
 

Job details:

Terms of employment: Full time, permanent position
Hours: 35 hours per week.
Wage: $40/hour.
 

Business and work address: #1150 – 1650 Kingsway Avenue, Port Coquitlam, BC  V3C 3Y9

Please note that remote work is not an option for this position.

TO APPLY:
If you are an experienced Senior Web Developer with a passion for creating high-quality websites and are looking to join a reputable wholesale company, we would love to hear from you.

Please submit your resume and cover letter highlighting your experience and skills to the attention of Fei Li, at career@igenmobility.com

Thank you for your interest. Should you have any questions, please call us at tel 604-404-0005. We will only contact those whose applications we will be pursuing further.

We are looking for full-time Cement Finisher with a minimum 3 years experience.

Duties include:

check formwork, granular base and steel reinforcement materials and direct placement of concrete into forms or onto surfaces according to grade;
fill hollows and remove spots on freshly poured cement;
operate power vibrators to compact concrete;
level top surface concrete according to grade and depth specification;
work at heights, on scaffolding or swing stages;
impart desired finish to concrete surfaces using hand and power tools;
install anchor bolts, steel plates, door sills and other fixtures;
apply hardening and sealing components to cure surfaces;
waterproof, damp proof and restore surfaces;
repair, resurface and replace worn or damaged sections of concrete structures.
$32.73 per hour (as per collective agreement).

Special consideration will be given to the various underrepresented groups.

TO APPLY:
If you have the skills and experience required for this position, please forward your resume to:

E-mail: jen@jwebercontracting.com
